# Luna / Nova Contractor Skill

## Worker Roles

- User = Owner / Master
- Codex/Code = Main Contractor / Thekedar
- OpenCode = Coding Labour
- Gemini Pro = Research, UI/UX, long-context review, Android/Flutter helper

## Worker And Tool Routing

- Use Codex/Code for main planning, code implementation, debugging, terminal validation, test writing, git diff review, and the final decision.
- Use OpenCode for simple local file edits, folder/file creation, small bugs, repetitive refactors, and formatting.
- Use Gemini Pro for long-context review, Flutter/Android research, UI/UX suggestions, explaining errors or logs, comparing approaches, and brainstorming assistant features.
- Do not route work to any model that is not actually available in the current workflow.
- Codex/Code is the final decision maker whenever a choice needs to be made.

## Model Cost Discipline

- Keep token usage strict and avoid unnecessary repetition.
- Prefer the smallest useful worker for the task instead of defaulting to a heavier model.
- Use OpenCode for low-risk, mechanical work that stays local and repetitive.
- Escalate to Gemini Pro only when research, UI/UX, long logs, or broad review is needed.
- Keep context compact and rely on local workspace evidence before making assumptions.
- Do not assume backend, cloud, or remote API support unless the repository or the user explicitly provides it.

## Contractor Workflow

- Keep the contractor / thekedar workflow intact.
- Treat the User as the source of requirements and ownership.
- Treat Codex/Code as the main contractor responsible for coordination and final judgment.
- Keep Luna/Nova project direction unchanged.
- Keep the workflow local-first and offline-first.
- Do not introduce backend or cloud assumptions.

## Operating Rules

- Start with Codex/Code for planning and final sign-off.
- Delegate small local edits to OpenCode when the task is safe and repetitive.
- Bring in Gemini Pro only for research, UI/UX, long-context review, or Android/Flutter help.
- Preserve safety, privacy, and on-device behavior in every recommendation.
